HE ACCUSED THE PRIESTHOOD

1278
01:06:03,859 --> 01:06:05,349
OF WITHHOLDING
THE BREAD OF LIFE

1279
01:06:05,428 --> 01:06:07,988
FROM THE SPIRITUALLY
STARVING PEOPLE.

1280
01:06:08,264 --> 01:06:11,665
HE BELIEVED THAT THE BIBLE
WAS A SUPREME AUTHORITY

1281
01:06:11,734 --> 01:06:16,865
AND HE COMMISSIONED
THE TRANSLATION OF THE BIBLE.

1282
01:06:16,939 --> 01:06:19,669
HE HAD SOME FOLLOWERS
CALLED LOLLARDS

1283
01:06:19,742 --> 01:06:23,303
THAT WENT AROUND DISTRIBUTING
SCRIPTURE AND PREACHING.

1284
01:06:23,379 --> 01:06:25,813
THEY DID BELIEVE
IN BIBLE READING.

1285
01:06:25,881 --> 01:06:28,850
THEY DID READ WYCLIFF'S BIBLE

1286
01:06:28,918 --> 01:06:34,379
AND THEY DID BELIEVE
IN THE SAME KIND OF SIMPLER PIETY

1287
01:06:34,457 --> 01:06:38,757
THAT THE WALDENSIANS
AND OTHERS HAD ADVOCATED

1288
01:06:38,828 --> 01:06:40,819
AS EARLY AS THE 1 2TH CENTURY.

1289
01:06:40,896 --> 01:06:42,693
THIS WAS THE GREATEST GIFT

1290
01:06:42,765 --> 01:06:44,790
HE COULD GIVE
THE COMMON PEOPLE.

1291
01:06:44,867 --> 01:06:47,597
NO DOCUMENT HAS ALTERED
THE COURSE OF HISTORY

1292
01:06:47,670 --> 01:06:51,265
MORE THAN THE ENGLISH
TRANSLATION OF THE BIBLE.

1293
01:06:51,340 --> 01:06:54,036
HE BROUGHT FORWARD
SOME OF THE TRUTHS

1294
01:06:54,310 --> 01:06:56,972
THAT PROTESTANTISM
WOULD LATER BRING FORWARD

1295
01:06:57,046 --> 01:06:58,741
AND AS I JUST SUGGESTED,

1296
01:06:58,814 --> 01:07:01,840
HIS TEACHINGS, EVEN THOUGH
IT'S CENTURIES BEFORE,

1297
01:07:01,917 --> 01:07:05,876
IS PREPARING THE WAY
FOR MANY PEOPLE IN ENGLAND

1298
01:07:05,955 --> 01:07:08,981
TO ACCEPT THE REFORMATION
WHEN IT COMES.

1299
01:07:09,058 --> 01:07:10,548
WYCLIFF HAD THE AUDACITY

1300
01:07:10,626 --> 01:07:13,720
TO DECLARE THAT THE UNIVERSAL
AUTHORITY OF THE POPE

1301
01:07:13,796 --> 01:07:15,320
WAS UNBIBLICAL.

1302
01:07:15,398 --> 01:07:19,858
IT WAS UNDER THESE CONDITIONS
THAT ON MAY 22, 13<i>77</i>

1303
01:07:19,935 --> 01:07:21,698
POPE GREGORY THE 1 1 TH

1304
01:07:21,771 --> 01:07:23,966
CONDEMNED THE WRITINGS
OF JOHN WYCLIFF

1305
01:07:24,040 --> 01:07:25,837
STATING THAT HIS TEACHINGS

1306
01:07:25,908 --> 01:07:28,672
WERE DANGEROUS
TO THE CHURCH AND THE STATE.

1307
01:07:28,744 --> 01:07:32,339
WYCLIFF CONTINUED TO TEACH
SALVATION THROUGH CHRIST ALONE

1308
01:07:32,415 --> 01:07:34,645
AND THAT THE SCRIPTURES
WERE INFALLIBLE

1309
01:07:34,717 --> 01:07:36,810
RATHER THAN THE ROMAN CHURCH.

1310
01:07:36,886 --> 01:07:40,083
OVER TIME, HIS WRITINGS
AND WORK OF REFORM

1311
01:07:40,356 --> 01:07:42,517
SPREAD OUT LIKE SEISMIC WAVES

1312
01:07:42,591 --> 01:07:45,424
INFLUENCING MILLIONS
OF GOD'S PEOPLE.

1313
01:07:45,494 --> 01:07:49,021
THEY CAN BE READ ANYWHERE
WHERE THERE ARE SCHOOLMEN,

1314
01:07:49,098 --> 01:07:53,057
WHERE THERE ARE SCHOLASTIC
THEOLOGIANS WHO CAN PICK THEM UP.

1315
01:07:53,135 --> 01:07:53,335
THEY DO TRAVEL
AND THEY TRAVEL TO BOHEMIA

1316
01:07:53,335 --> 01:07:55,735
THEY DO TRAVEL
AND THEY TRAVEL TO BOHEMIA

1317
01:07:55,805 --> 01:07:59,536
AND THEY INSPIRE
JOHN HUSS AS WELL.

1318
01:07:59,608 --> 01:08:04,705
AND HUSS SHARES THE ATTACK
ON TRANSUBSTANTIATION,

1319
01:08:04,780 --> 01:08:09,513
ON CLERICAL POWER
AND ON, AS WITH WYCLIFF,

1320
01:08:09,585 --> 01:08:11,450
ON THE WEALTH OF THE CHURCH.

1321
01:08:11,520 --> 01:08:15,388
HUSS WAS ONLY A YOUNG BOY
WHEN WYCLIFF PASSED AWAY,

1322
01:08:15,458 --> 01:08:17,790
BUT WYCLIFF'S WORKS
HAD A POWERFUL INFLUENCE

1323
01:08:17,860 --> 01:08:20,658
ON HIS LIFE
AND HIS FUTURE MISSION.

1324
01:08:20,729 --> 01:08:24,426
JOHN HUSS
WAS A BOHEMIAN PREACHER,

1325
01:08:24,500 --> 01:08:25,865
ALSO A UNIVERSITY PROFESSOR

1326
01:08:25,935 --> 01:08:27,562
AND ALSO
KING'S CHAPLAIN FOR AWHILE.

1327
01:08:27,636 --> 01:08:34,132
HE'S ENTRUSTED, EVENTUALLY
WITH THE OFFICE OF PREACHING

1328
01:08:34,410 --> 01:08:38,870
AT A LITTLE CHAPEL
THAT HAS JUST BEEN FOUNDED,

1329
01:08:38,948 --> 01:08:40,848
THE BETHLEHEM CHAPEL.

1330
01:08:40,916 --> 01:08:43,714
LIKE WYCLIFF, JOHN HUSS
PREACHED THE SCRIPTURES

1331
01:08:43,786 --> 01:08:45,413
IN THE LANGUAGE OF THE PEOPLE

1332
01:08:45,488 --> 01:08:47,615
A PRACTICE THAT THE CHURCH
HAD NOW FORBIDDEN

1333
01:08:47,690 --> 01:08:50,386
IN FAVOR
OF THE LOST LANGUAGE OF LATIN.

1334
01:08:50,459 --> 01:08:52,757
HE DID PREACH
IN THE VERNACULAR LANGUAGE

1335
01:08:52,828 --> 01:08:57,959
AND THE BOHEMIANS HAD HAD
SCRIPTURE IN THEIR LANGUAGE

1336
01:08:58,033 --> 01:08:59,625
DESPITE CHURCH COUNCILS.

1337
01:08:59,702 --> 01:09:01,033
AND IT'S FROM THAT

1338
01:09:01,103 --> 01:09:05,039
THAT HE COMES INTO CONTACT
WITH THE TEACHINGS OF WYCLIFF

1339
01:09:05,107 --> 01:09:11,979
AND HE ESPECIALLY IS DRAWN TO
THE ATTACK ON TRANSUBSTANTIATION,

1340
01:09:12,047 --> 01:09:16,108
ON THE ATTACK ON THE WEALTH
AND INFLUENCE OF THE CHURCH.

1341
01:09:16,185 --> 01:09:19,848
WALKING THROUGH TOWN ONE DAY,
HUSS NOTICED A COUPLE OF PAINTINGS

1342
01:09:19,922 --> 01:09:24,086
THAT TWO MEN HAD DISPLAYED
AS A SILENT PROTEST.

1343
01:09:24,160 --> 01:09:27,652
EACH OF THE CANVASES
PORTRAYED A DIFFERENT SCENE.

1344
01:09:27,730 --> 01:09:30,995
ON ONE WAS THE IMAGE
OF THE LOWLY JESUS

1345
01:09:31,066 --> 01:09:35,196
HUMBLY ENTERING JERUSALEM
WITH HIS TRAVEL-WORN DISCIPLES.

1346
01:09:35,471 --> 01:09:38,531
ON THE OTHER CANVAS
WAS AN IMAGE OF THE POPE

1347
01:09:38,607 --> 01:09:41,041
DRESSED IN RICH
AND LUXURIOUS CLOTHING,

1348
01:09:41,110 --> 01:09:42,668
CARRIED ON A LITTER

1349
01:09:42,745 --> 01:09:44,838
AND FOLLOWED
BY A REGAL PROCESSION.

1350
01:09:44,914 --> 01:09:47,747
THE PAINTINGS CERTAINLY
PRESENTED A CONTRAST

1351
01:09:47,816 --> 01:09:49,181
BETWEEN JESUS,

1352
01:09:49,251 --> 01:09:51,617
WHO SAID
THAT FOXES HAVE HOLES

1353
01:09:51,687 --> 01:09:53,120
AND THE BIRDS
OF THE AIR HAVE NESTS

1354
01:09:53,189 --> 01:09:56,215
AND THE SON OF MAN
HAS NOWHERE TO LAY HIS HEAD,

1355
01:09:56,492 --> 01:09:58,858
WITH THE MAGNIFICENT SPLENDOR

1356
01:09:58,928 --> 01:10:03,126
OF THE PAPAL PALACE
AND THE PAPAL ENTOURAGE.

1357
01:10:03,199 --> 01:10:04,894
MOVED BY THIS KNOWLEDGE,

1358
01:10:04,967 --> 01:10:07,800
HE BEGAN TO PUBLICLY DENOUNCE
THE PRIDE, AMBITION,

1359
01:10:07,870 --> 01:10:09,770
AND CORRUPTION OF THE CLERGY

1360
01:10:09,838 --> 01:10:13,137
AND HE FEARLESSLY CALLED
FOR THE CHURCH TO REFORM.

1361
01:10:13,209 --> 01:10:16,110
IF YOU MUST INTERPRET SCRIPTURE
ACCORDING TO TRUTH,

1362
01:10:16,178 --> 01:10:20,114
TRUTH IS DEFINED
BY WHAT THE CHURCH BELIEVES.

1363
01:10:20,182 --> 01:10:23,151
HOW DO YOU CORRECT
AN ERROR IN THE CHURCH?

1364
01:10:23,219 --> 01:10:25,949
YOU DON'T HAVE
A CHECK ON MISTAKES.

1365
01:10:26,021 --> 01:10:28,012
THERE IS NO CORRECTING
THE CHURCH.

1366
01:10:28,090 --> 01:10:31,651
AND THAT, I THINK,
IS THE FUNDAMENTAL FLAW

1367
01:10:31,727 --> 01:10:36,790
OF WHAT ALLOWED THE CHURCH
TO START GOING WRONG

1368
01:10:36,865 --> 01:10:39,060
AND KEEP GOING WRONG.

1369
01:10:39,134 --> 01:10:42,262
JOHN HUSS WAS INVITED
TO COME TO CONSTANCE, GERMANY

1370
01:10:42,538 --> 01:10:45,200
TO DEFEND HIS CRITICISM
OF THE CHURCH OF ROME.

1371
01:10:45,274 --> 01:10:49,506
SIGISMUND, KING OF HUNGARY,
AND LATER, THE HOLY ROMAN EMPIRE

1372
01:10:49,578 --> 01:10:52,069
GUARANTEED HIM A SAFE PASSAGE,

1373
01:10:52,147 --> 01:10:55,207
BUT IMMEDIATELY
UPON HUSS' ARRIVAL IN THE CITY,

1374
01:10:55,284 --> 01:10:57,775
HE WAS ARRESTED
AND PLACED IN THE DUNGEON

1375
01:10:57,853 --> 01:10:59,718
AT GOTTLIEBEN CASTLE.

1376
01:10:59,788 --> 01:11:01,915
KING SIGISMUND
WAS GREATLY ANGERED

1377
01:11:01,991 --> 01:11:03,583
AT THE IMPRISONMENT OF HUSS

1378
01:11:03,659 --> 01:11:05,650
AND HE THREATENED
THE CHURCH COUNCIL

1379
01:11:05,728 --> 01:11:07,889
BUT THE COUNCIL
CONVINCED SIGISMUND

1380
01:11:07,963 --> 01:11:11,592
THAT PROMISES MADE
TO A HERETIC WERE NOT BINDING.

1381
01:11:11,667 --> 01:11:15,125
ON JULY 6, 1 <i>4</i>1<i>5</i>,
THE COUNCIL GATHERED

1382
01:11:15,204 --> 01:11:18,230
INTO THE CATHEDRAL
AFTER MASS AND LITURGY

1383
01:11:18,307 --> 01:11:22,038
AND JOHN HUSS
WAS THEN LED IN FOR HIS TRIAL.

1384
01:11:22,111 --> 01:11:25,911
HE WAS ASKED
TO DEFEND HIS POSITIONS.

1385
01:11:25,981 --> 01:11:28,575
IN THE ACT OF DEFENDING THEM

1386
01:11:28,651 --> 01:11:31,711
HE WAS FOUND
TO HAVE VOICED A HERESY

1387
01:11:31,787 --> 01:11:36,724
AND SO HE WAS SEIZED
AND TRIED FOR HERESY.

1388
01:11:36,792 --> 01:11:40,819
GUARDS THEN LED HUSS
AWAY TO BE EXECUTED.

1389
01:11:40,896 --> 01:11:44,559
AT THE PLACE OF HIS EXECUTION,
HUSS STOOD FIRM.

1390
01:11:44,633 --> 01:11:46,863
AS THE FLAMES ROSE ABOUT HIM,

1391
01:11:46,935 --> 01:11:51,133
HE WAS ACTUALLY
ABLE TO LIFT HIS VOICE IN SONG.

1392
01:11:51,206 --> 01:11:54,073
AMONG HIS DYING WORDS,
HUSS PREDICTED,

1393
01:11:54,143 --> 01:11:56,976
''IN A HUNDRED YEARS
GOD WILL RAISE UP A MAN

1394
01:11:57,046 --> 01:12:00,345
WHOSE CALLS FOR REFORM
CANNOT BE SUPPRESSED.''

1395
01:12:02,217 --> 01:12:05,152
RAISED IN A HUMBLE HOME
IN MANSFIELD, GERMANY,

1396
01:12:05,220 --> 01:12:07,984
MARTIN LUTHER, THEOLOGIAN,
AUTHOR, COMPOSER,

1397
01:12:08,057 --> 01:12:09,991
AND PRIEST WAS ARGUABLY

1398
01:12:10,059 --> 01:12:12,027
THE BEST KNOWN
RELIGIOUS REFORMER

1399
01:12:12,094 --> 01:12:14,688
OF THE 1 6TH CENTURY.

1400
01:12:14,763 --> 01:12:18,790
LUTHER WAS BORN
ON NOVEMBER 1 0, 1 <i>48</i>3,

1401
01:12:18,867 --> 01:12:22,894
NEARLY <i>7</i>0 YEARS
AFTER THE MARTYRDOM OF JOHN HUSS.

1402
01:12:22,971 --> 01:12:25,235
BORN INTO A HARDWORKING
MIDDLE-CLASS FAMILY,

1403
01:12:25,307 --> 01:12:27,605
WITH SEVERAL
BROTHERS AND SISTERS,

1404
01:12:27,676 --> 01:12:31,009
LUTHER DEVELOPED A FIRM
CHARACTER AND PERSONALITY.

1405
01:12:31,080 --> 01:12:34,049
THE LUTHER FAMILY
SEEMS TO HAVE BEEN,

1406
01:12:34,116 --> 01:12:37,017
TO SOME EXTENT,
A FAMILY OF OVER-ACHIEVERS.

1407
01:12:37,086 --> 01:12:38,610
THEY WERE VERY STRICT,

1408
01:12:38,687 --> 01:12:40,279
ACCORDING
TO LUTHER'S LATER STORIES.

1409
01:12:40,356 --> 01:12:42,824
THEY WERE VERY STRICT
ON THE YOUNG MARTIN

1410
01:12:42,891 --> 01:12:44,620
AND THEY CERTAINLY SAW

1411
01:12:44,693 --> 01:12:48,254
THAT THE WAY FORWARD FOR THEIR SON
WAS THROUGH EDUCATION.

1412
01:12:48,330 --> 01:12:50,025
BUT WHEN HE WAS YOUNG,

1413
01:12:50,099 --> 01:12:53,227
HE WAS INTENDED
TO BECOME A LAWYER.

1414
01:12:53,302 --> 01:12:54,997
HOWEVER,
A DRAMATIC EXPERIENCE

1415
01:12:55,070 --> 01:12:58,699
FOREVER ALTERED
THE COURSE OF HIS LIFE.

1416
01:12:58,774 --> 01:13:03,734
LUTHER IS CAUGHT IN A THUNDERSTORM
AND FEARS FOR HIS LIFE.

1417
01:13:03,812 --> 01:13:06,838
HE'S OUTSIDE AND HE FEARS
HE'LL BE STRUCK BY LIGHTNING.

1418
01:13:06,915 --> 01:13:09,281
LIGHTNING WAS STRIKING
IN FRONT OF HIM AND BEHIND HIM

1419
01:13:09,351 --> 01:13:13,185
AND ON BOTH SIDES OF HIM
AND SO IN TERROR HE CRIES OUT

1420
01:13:13,255 --> 01:13:15,689
AND PROMISES
THAT IF A SAINT WILL SAVE HIM,

1421
01:13:15,758 --> 01:13:17,385
HE WILL BECOME A MONK.

1422
01:13:17,459 --> 01:13:23,295
HE CALLED OUT TO SAINT ANNE,
THE SAINT OF HOPELESS CAUSES.

1423
01:13:23,365 --> 01:13:28,667
''SAINT ANNE, DELIVER ME
AND I'LL BECOME A MONK<i>!</i>''

1424
01:13:28,737 --> 01:13:30,671
AND HE KEPT HIS WORD.

1425
01:13:30,739 --> 01:13:33,071
IN SPITE
OF HIS FATHER'S ANGRY PROTESTS,

1426
01:13:33,142 --> 01:13:36,009
LUTHER DROPPED
HIS LAW STUDIES, SOLD HIS BOOKS,

1427
01:13:36,078 --> 01:13:39,707
AND ENTERED A CLOSED
AUGUSTINIAN MONASTERY AT ERFURT

1428
01:13:39,782 --> 01:13:43,411
AND FULLY DEDICATED HIS TIME
TO THE MONASTIC LIFE.

1429
01:13:43,485 --> 01:13:46,682
FOLLOWING HIS DESPERATE
LONGING FOR SALVATION,

1430
01:13:46,755 --> 01:13:50,020
HE PRACTICED FREQUENT FASTINGS,
LONG HOURS OF PRAYER,

1431
01:13:50,092 --> 01:13:52,890
AUSTERE LIVING
AND ENDLESS CONFESSION.

1432
01:13:55,798 --> 01:13:58,995
''IF ANYONE COULD HAVE GAINED
HEAVEN AS A MONK

1433
01:13:59,067 --> 01:14:01,797
THEN I WOULD, INDEED,
HAVE BEEN AMONG THEM.''

1434
01:14:01,870 --> 01:14:05,203
HE FOUND
AN ELDER CONFESSOR THERE

1435
01:14:05,274 --> 01:14:09,233
WHO REALIZED THAT LUTHER
HAD A PARTICULARLY SENSITIVE SOUL

1436
01:14:09,311 --> 01:14:10,972
AND THIS CONFESSOR REALIZED

1437
01:14:11,046 --> 01:14:14,174
THAT LUTHER
NEEDED TO TEACH THE BIBLE.

1438
01:14:14,249 --> 01:14:20,085
SO HE BECOMES SIMULTANEOUSLY
PROFESSOR OF THEOLOGY,

1439
01:14:20,155 --> 01:14:22,282
PREACHER IN THE TOWN CHURCH,

1440
01:14:22,357 --> 01:14:24,723
AND A MEMBER
OF THE RELIGIOUS COMMUNITY

1441
01:14:24,793 --> 01:14:26,852
IN THE AUGUSTINIAN HOUSE.

1442
01:14:26,929 --> 01:14:29,955
HE'S BASICALLY DOING THREE JOBS.

1443
01:14:30,032 --> 01:14:32,830
AT WITTENBERG HE LEARNED
TO STUDY THE BIBLE

1444
01:14:32,901 --> 01:14:34,732
IN ITS ORIGINAL TONGUES.

1445
01:14:34,803 --> 01:14:37,863
SOON, HE BEGAN
TO FREELY SHARE THE TRUTHS

1446
01:14:37,940 --> 01:14:39,908
THAT HE WAS LEARNING
IN HIS LECTURES

1447
01:14:39,975 --> 01:14:42,205
AND HIS LISTENERS
WERE DELIGHTED.

1448
01:14:42,277 --> 01:14:45,075
IN 1<i>5</i>1 0,
LUTHER MADE A PILGRIMAGE

1449
01:14:45,147 --> 01:14:46,944
TO VISIT THE HEADQUARTERS
OF THE CHURCH

1450
01:14:47,015 --> 01:14:49,006
IN THE HOLY CITY OF ROME.

1451
01:14:49,084 --> 01:14:52,247
HE WAS SICKENED TO WITNESS
THE TERRIBLE GREED AND WICKEDNESS

1452
01:14:52,321 --> 01:14:55,950
THAT HE SAW
AMONG ALL CLASSES OF THE CLERGY.

1453
01:14:56,024 --> 01:14:58,254
HIS GREAT EXPECTATION
OF THE HOLY CITY

1454
01:14:58,327 --> 01:14:59,919
WAS CRUSHED AS HE BEHELD

1455
01:14:59,995 --> 01:15:03,897
THE DECADENT LIFESTYLES
OF THE MONKS AND THE PRIESTS.

1456
01:15:03,966 --> 01:15:05,297
THIS WAS IN STARK CONTRAST

1457
01:15:05,367 --> 01:15:08,234
TO HIS VERY
FRUGAL LIFE IN GERMANY.

1458
01:15:08,303 --> 01:15:10,863
BUT LUTHER'S
MOST UNSETTLING REVELATION

1459
01:15:10,939 --> 01:15:13,237
WAS YET TO COME.

1460
01:15:13,308 --> 01:15:16,175
HE WENT TO ROME AND HE WAS
CLIMBING UP THE STAIRS THERE

1461
01:15:16,245 --> 01:15:17,837
AND HEARS A VOICE-

1462
01:15:17,913 --> 01:15:20,438
NOT NECESSARILY A VERBAL ONE,
BUT ONE IN HIS HEAD-

1463
01:15:20,516 --> 01:15:22,347
''THE JUST SHALL LIVE BY FAITH.''

1464
01:15:22,417 --> 01:15:26,046
AND SO CLIMBING UP THESE,
PILATE'S STAIRS, ON HIS KNEES,

1465
01:15:26,121 --> 01:15:29,284
WHICH WAS SUPPOSED TO EARN YOU
SOME KIND OF ASSURANCE

1466
01:15:29,358 --> 01:15:32,452
OF NOT BURNING
IN PURGATORY FOR TOO LONG.

1467
01:15:32,528 --> 01:15:35,497
AND IT JUST DAWNED ON HIM
AS HE LOOKED AROUND,

1468
01:15:35,564 --> 01:15:37,225
''WHAT ARE WE DOING?

1469
01:15:37,299 --> 01:15:40,166
THE BIBLE SAYS
THIS COMES BY FAITH.''

1470
01:15:40,235 --> 01:15:42,169
AND HE GOT UP OFF HIS KNEES

1471
01:15:42,237 --> 01:15:44,228
AND THIS SEEMED TO BE
A TURNING POINT.

1472
01:15:44,306 --> 01:15:45,898
LUTHER FINALLY UNDERSTOOD

1473
01:15:45,974 --> 01:15:48,499
THE IMPORTANCE OF TRUSTING
IN THE MERITS OF CHRIST

1474
01:15:48,577 --> 01:15:50,943
FOR FORGIVENESS.

1475
01:15:51,013 --> 01:15:53,914
AFTER RETURNING FROM ROME IN 1<i>5</i>1 2,

1476
01:15:53,982 --> 01:15:56,212
LUTHER WAS AWARDED
THE DOCTORATE OF DIVINITY

1477
01:15:56,285 --> 01:15:58,378
AT THE UNIVERSITY OF WITTENBERG

1478
01:15:58,453 --> 01:16:01,115
AND HE BEGAN
TO BOLDLY PREACH TO THE PEOPLE

1479
01:16:01,189 --> 01:16:04,124
THAT CHRISTIANS SHOULD NOT
ACCEPT ANY DOCTRINE

1480
01:16:04,192 --> 01:16:06,820
UNLESS IT CAME FROM THE BIBLE

1481
01:16:06,895 --> 01:16:10,126
AND IT WAS THIS PRINCIPLE
OF ''SOLA SCRIPTURA''

1482
01:16:10,198 --> 01:16:13,292
THAT WOULD BECOME THE BATTLE CRY
OF THE REFORMATION.

1483
01:16:13,368 --> 01:16:18,169
IT'S IN A SERIES
OF THREE TREATISES IN 1<i>5</i>20

1484
01:16:18,240 --> 01:16:22,370
THAT HE PRESENTS
THE NOTION THAT NOW,

1485
01:16:22,444 --> 01:16:24,412
SINCE THE TRADITION
OF THE CHURCH

1486
01:16:24,479 --> 01:16:28,472
HAS BECOME SO CORRUPTED
BY HUMAN INNOVATION,

1487
01:16:28,550 --> 01:16:31,314
THAT THE CHURCH
SHOULD ONLY FOLLOW

1488
01:16:31,386 --> 01:16:33,581
THE TESTIMONY OF THE SCRIPTURES.

1489
01:16:33,655 --> 01:16:36,852
THIS IS THE COMMON THREAD

1490
01:16:36,925 --> 01:16:41,294
IN THE STORY THAT DESCRIBES
THE DECLINE OF THE CHURCH.

1491
01:16:41,363 --> 01:16:43,388
IT'S WHEN PEOPLE LOST SCRIPTURE

1492
01:16:43,465 --> 01:16:45,365
AND THE ABILITY TO READ
SCRIPTURE FOR THEMSELVES

1493
01:16:45,434 --> 01:16:46,924
AND THERE WAS A BARRIER

1494
01:16:47,002 --> 01:16:48,902
BETWEEN THEM AND SCRIPTURE
AND THEM AND CHRIST.

1495
01:16:48,971 --> 01:16:51,462
AND THEN IT BEGAN TO RECOVER

1496
01:16:51,540 --> 01:16:53,440
WHEN MARTIN LUTHER
AND HIS COLLEAGUES

1497
01:16:53,508 --> 01:16:56,170
DECIDED THAT SCRIPTURE
REALLY WAS THE AUTHORITY,

1498
01:16:56,244 --> 01:17:00,237
''SOLA SCRIPTURA,
TOTA SCRIPTURA, PRIMA SCRIPTURA''

1499
01:17:00,315 --> 01:17:03,910
AND THEY BEGAN
TO CLIMB BACK OUT.

1500
01:17:03,986 --> 01:17:05,578
ABOUT THIS SAME TIME,

1501
01:17:05,654 --> 01:17:07,918
ROME WAS BREAKING GROUND
FOR THE CONSTRUCTION

1502
01:17:07,990 --> 01:17:11,619
OF THE MAGNIFICENT
NEW SAINT PETER'S BASILICA.

1503
01:17:11,693 --> 01:17:14,423
THE CHURCH SENT JOHN TETZEL,
A DOMINICAN FRIAR,

1504
01:17:14,496 --> 01:17:17,624
TO GERMANY
TO SELL INDULGENCES

1505
01:17:17,699 --> 01:17:21,567
IN ORDER TO RAISE THE FUNDS
NECESSARY FOR THE CATHEDRAL.

1506
01:17:21,637 --> 01:17:23,104
THE CHURCH BELIEVES,

1507
01:17:23,171 --> 01:17:25,332
NOT ONLY
THAT ITS SERVICES AND OFFERINGS

1508
01:17:25,407 --> 01:17:26,931
CAN HELP THE DEAD,

1509
01:17:27,009 --> 01:17:30,968
BUT ALSO THAT THE HEAD
OF THE CHURCH IN THE WEST, THE POPE,

1510
01:17:31,046 --> 01:17:36,109
CAN, OUT OF THE SUPER
ABUNDANCE OF SAVED UP GRACE,

1511
01:17:36,184 --> 01:17:38,914
WHICH IS IN THE POSSESSION
OF THE CHURCH,

1512
01:17:38,987 --> 01:17:40,921
THE CHURCH
CAN SIMPLY DECLARE

1513
01:17:40,989 --> 01:17:46,052
THAT SOMEONE'S PENALTIES
OWED AFTER THEY DIED

1514
01:17:46,128 --> 01:17:47,561
ARE JUST WIPED OUT.

1515
01:17:47,629 --> 01:17:50,427
THAT'S WHAT'S CALLED
AN INDULGENCE.

1516
01:17:50,499 --> 01:17:53,024
THE FULL PLENARY INDULGENCE

1517
01:17:53,101 --> 01:17:55,399
ABSOLVED A PERSON
OF ALL THE SINS

1518
01:17:55,470 --> 01:17:59,270
THAT THEY HAD COMMITTED
UP TO THAT TIME

1519
01:17:59,341 --> 01:18:04,074
AND THUS SPEEDED YOU,
ACCORDING TO CHURCH TEACHING,

1520
01:18:04,146 --> 01:18:08,173
THROUGH PURGATORY
DIRECTLY INTO HEAVEN.

1521
01:18:08,250 --> 01:18:10,548
BY VERY LATE
IN THE MIDDLE AGES,

1522
01:18:10,619 --> 01:18:13,383
THE CHURCH
HAS GOT INTO ITS HEAD

1523
01:18:13,455 --> 01:18:17,448
THAT IT CAN SAY TO PEOPLE,

1524
01:18:17,526 --> 01:18:18,993
''IF YOU ARE WILLING

1525
01:18:19,061 --> 01:18:22,428
''TO MAKE AN OFFERING
TO THE CHURCH,

1526
01:18:22,497 --> 01:18:24,590
''THE CHURCH
WILL GIVE AN INDULGENCE

1527
01:18:24,666 --> 01:18:26,657
''IN THE MANNER OF AN OFFERING,

1528
01:18:26,735 --> 01:18:32,537
''FOR YOUR DEPARTED FAMILY,
FRIEND, RELATIVE, LOVED ONE

1529
01:18:32,607 --> 01:18:36,373
AND THAT LOVED ONE WILL ESCAPE
THE PAINS OF PURGATORY,''

1530
01:18:36,445 --> 01:18:38,379
SUPPOSEDLY IMMEDIATELY.

1531
01:18:38,447 --> 01:18:41,712
THIS BECAME,
BY THE 1 <i>4</i>TH AND 1<i>5</i>TH CENTURY,

1532
01:18:41,783 --> 01:18:44,047
A VERY POPULAR BELIEF

1533
01:18:44,119 --> 01:18:47,145
AND PEOPLE
CLAMORED FOR INDULGENCES.

1534
01:18:47,222 --> 01:18:48,519
WHEN LUTHER LEARNED

1535
01:18:48,590 --> 01:18:50,990
THAT HIS MEMBERS
WERE PURCHASING INDULGENCES,

1536
01:18:51,059 --> 01:18:52,583
HE WAS OUTRAGED.

1537
01:18:52,661 --> 01:18:56,119
AS THE PEOPLE CAME TO HIM
TO CASH IN THEIR INDULGENCES,

1538
01:18:56,198 --> 01:18:58,564
HE FLATLY REFUSED
TO HONOR THEM.

1539
01:18:58,633 --> 01:19:01,568
LUTHER DECLARED
THAT WHAT THEY REALLY NEEDED TO DO

1540
01:19:01,636 --> 01:19:05,538
WAS TO SINCERELY REPENT
AND TURN FROM THEIR SINS.

1541
01:19:05,607 --> 01:19:09,236
THIS WAS THE FIRST ISSUE
THAT FORCED LUTHER INTO BATTLE

1542
01:19:09,311 --> 01:19:11,575
WITH HIS OWN BELOVED CHURCH.

1543
01:19:11,646 --> 01:19:14,615
ON OCTOBER 31 , 1<i>5</i>1 <i>7</i>,

1544
01:19:14,683 --> 01:19:16,708
LUTHER NAILED
HIS FAMOUS PROTEST

1545
01:19:16,785 --> 01:19:20,721
TO THE DOORS OF ALL THE SAINTS
CHURCH IN WITTENBERG.

1546
01:19:20,789 --> 01:19:23,485
WHAT ARE THE 9<i>5</i> THESES
THAT HE FAMOUSLY NAILS

1547
01:19:23,558 --> 01:19:26,026
TO THE DOOR
OF WITTENBERG CASTLE CHURCH?

1548
01:19:26,094 --> 01:19:29,063
IT'S AN ACADEMIC INVITATION
TO A DEBATE.

1549
01:19:29,131 --> 01:19:31,793
YOU WRITE DOWN
9<i>5</i> THESIS STATEMENTS

1550
01:19:32,067 --> 01:19:34,729
AND YOU'RE BASICALLY SAYING,
''HERE ARE MY PROPOSALS''

1551
01:19:34,803 --> 01:19:37,203
AND THEY'RE ALWAYS
MORE STRONGLY WORDED

1552
01:19:37,272 --> 01:19:39,433
THAN YOU MAY THINK
BECAUSE IT'S A DEBATING POINT;

1553
01:19:39,508 --> 01:19:42,477
IT'S WHAT'S CALLED A DISPUTATION.

1554
01:19:42,544 --> 01:19:48,642
THE 9<i>5</i> THESES IS JUST
A SERIES OF 9<i>5</i> PROPOSITIONS

1555
01:19:48,717 --> 01:19:53,051
THAT HE INTENDS TO SPARK
A UNIVERSITY DEBATE ON.

1556
01:19:53,121 --> 01:20:00,050
AND THIS IS STANDARD ISSUE
LATE MEDIEVAL ACADEMIC PRACTICE.

1557
01:20:00,796 --> 01:20:02,525
SO LUTHER IS ENGAGING

1558
01:20:02,597 --> 01:20:05,566
IN A VERY NARROWLY
ACADEMIC EXERCISE.

1559
01:20:05,634 --> 01:20:09,161
IT'S LIKE PUBLISHING A PAPER
IN A SCHOLARLY JOURNAL TODAY.

1560
01:20:09,237 --> 01:20:10,636
AS A HISTORIAN MYSELF AT TIMES,

1561
01:20:10,705 --> 01:20:13,265
YOU'RE NOT ACTUALLY EXPECTING
VERY MANY PEOPLE TO READ THIS,

1562
01:20:13,341 --> 01:20:16,174
YOU'RE JUST GOING
INTO A VERY NARROW CIRCLE.

1563
01:20:16,244 --> 01:20:18,735
SO HE TAKES IT
AND HE NAILS IT TO THE DOOR

1564
01:20:18,814 --> 01:20:20,406
OF WITTENBERG CASTLE CHURCH

1565
01:20:20,482 --> 01:20:21,744
BECAUSE THAT'S
THE TRADITIONAL PLACE

1566
01:20:21,817 --> 01:20:24,445
YOU POST INVITATIONS
FOR A DISPUTATION.

1567
01:20:24,519 --> 01:20:27,420
SO HE'S NOT EXPECTING ANYTHING,
NECESSARILY, TO COME OF THIS.

1568
01:20:27,489 --> 01:20:29,389
AND THIS GOT
A LOT OF PEOPLE'S ATTENTION,

1569
01:20:29,457 --> 01:20:31,118
INCLUDING THE POPE'S.

1570
01:20:31,193 --> 01:20:33,388
AS FAR AS LUTHER'S CONCERNED,
HE'S NOT PROMOTING SOMETHING

1571
01:20:33,461 --> 01:20:36,191
THAT THE CHURCH
WOULD BE HOSTILE TO,

1572
01:20:36,264 --> 01:20:38,528
HE BELIEVES HE'S PROMOTING THINGS
THAT THE CHURCH WILL WELCOME.

1573
01:20:38,600 --> 01:20:41,660
AND, INDEED, IF YOU GO BACK
TO THE EARLY CHURCH FATHERS,

1574
01:20:41,736 --> 01:20:43,294
INCLUDING AUGUSTINE,

1575
01:20:43,371 --> 01:20:45,464
YOU CAN FIND
MANY THINGS IN THEIR WRITINGS

1576
01:20:45,540 --> 01:20:46,871
IN ACCORD WITH LUTHER'S IDEAS.

1577
01:20:47,142 --> 01:20:49,337
SO LUTHER ACTUALLY EXPECTS
PEOPLE TO SORT OF SAY,

1578
01:20:49,411 --> 01:20:52,505
''OH, GREAT.
THANKS FOR POINTING THAT OUT.''

1579
01:20:52,581 --> 01:20:54,139
WHICH WAS PERHAPS A TRIFLE NA<i></i>VE

1580
01:20:54,216 --> 01:20:58,414
AND PERHAPS THAT'S WHAT COMES
FROM HIM BEING AN ACADEMIC.

1581
01:20:58,486 --> 01:21:02,513
BUT LUTHER IS NOT TRYING
TO SET UP ANOTHER MOVEMENT-

1582
01:21:02,591 --> 01:21:03,853
JUST THE OPPOSITE.

1583
01:21:03,925 --> 01:21:05,552
BUT THE REALITY, OF COURSE,

1584
01:21:05,627 --> 01:21:07,356
IS THAT THE CHURCH
DOES NOT WELCOME

1585
01:21:07,429 --> 01:21:09,294
MUCH OF WHAT LUTHER
HAS TO SAY.

1586
01:21:09,364 --> 01:21:11,355
AND A BULL WENT OUT-

1587
01:21:11,433 --> 01:21:14,459
A PAPAL BULL
MEANING A KIND OF DECLARATION -

1588
01:21:14,536 --> 01:21:16,697
CONDEMNING LUTHER
AND HIS WRITINGS

1589
01:21:16,771 --> 01:21:21,208
AND SAYING THEY SHOULD BE
CONSIGNED TO THE FLAMES.

1590
01:21:21,276 --> 01:21:23,437
THE BULL WAS DELIVERED AT WITTENBERG

1591
01:21:23,511 --> 01:21:27,845
AND INSTEAD OF CONSIGNING
THE WRITINGS TO THE FLAMES,

1592
01:21:27,916 --> 01:21:30,851
LUTHER HAD A BIG GATHERING
IN WITTENBERG

1593
01:21:30,919 --> 01:21:33,353
AND CONSIGNED
THE BULL TO THE FLAMES

1594
01:21:33,421 --> 01:21:35,753
AND THERE WAS A BURNING
OF THIS PAPAL BULL

1595
01:21:35,824 --> 01:21:40,352
AND THIS, OF COURSE,
WAS A ''THROW DOWN'' NOW, RIGHT?

1596
01:21:40,428 --> 01:21:42,225
THE CHALLENGE
HAD BEEN SENT OUT

1597
01:21:42,297 --> 01:21:44,288
AND THE CHALLENGE
HAD BEEN RESPONDED TO.

1598
01:21:44,366 --> 01:21:45,663
AND THAT'S WHEN LUTHER SAYS,

1599
01:21:45,734 --> 01:21:48,202
''RIGHT, IF YOU CONDEMN ME
I WILL CONDEMN YOU,''

1600
01:21:48,270 --> 01:21:51,364
BECAUSE HE BELIEVES
THIS IS A MATTER OF TRUTH.

1601
01:21:51,439 --> 01:21:53,839
AND SO, IF THE CHURCH
IS CONDEMNING BIBLICAL TRUTH

1602
01:21:53,909 --> 01:21:56,673
THEN THE CHURCH
MUST ACTUALLY BE ANTICHRIST

1603
01:21:56,745 --> 01:21:58,713
AND HE CALLS IT THAT
AND, OF COURSE,

1604
01:21:58,780 --> 01:22:00,304
ONCE YOU CALL
SOMEBODY ANTICHRIST,

1605
01:22:00,382 --> 01:22:04,443
IT'S RATHER HARD TO REACH
CONSENSUS AND COMPROMISE.

1606
01:22:04,519 --> 01:22:06,783
SO THE GERMAN EMPEROR
ORGANIZED A HEARING

1607
01:22:06,855 --> 01:22:08,880
AND ALL THE IMPORTANT
PRINCES AND PRIESTS

1608
01:22:08,957 --> 01:22:11,824
WERE ASSEMBLED
FOR AN HISTORIC MEETING

1609
01:22:11,893 --> 01:22:13,656
AT A PLACE CALLED WORMS.

1610
01:22:13,728 --> 01:22:15,286
SO THERE WERE
REPRESENTATIVES HERE

1611
01:22:15,363 --> 01:22:17,388
OF ALL THE DIFFERENT
PRINCES, NOBLES,

1612
01:22:17,465 --> 01:22:19,933
AND FREE CITIES OF THE EMPIRE

1613
01:22:20,001 --> 01:22:23,869
AND LUTHER GOES, BELIEVING
HE'LL HAVE A CHANCE TO DEBATE.

1614
01:22:23,939 --> 01:22:25,964
THE CHURCH KNOWS
THAT LUTHER'S A BRILLIANT DEBATER

1615
01:22:26,241 --> 01:22:28,471
AND THEY'RE NOT
GOING TO GIVE HIM ANY CHANCE.

1616
01:22:28,543 --> 01:22:30,306
HE WAS PULLED UP
BEFORE THE GROUP.

1617
01:22:30,378 --> 01:22:32,608
HE WAS SHOWN
A PILE OF HIS BOOKS.

1618
01:22:32,681 --> 01:22:37,641
HE WAS ASKED TWO QUESTIONS:
''ARE THESE BOOKS YOURS?''

1619
01:22:37,719 --> 01:22:40,517
AND ''WILL YOU RECANT?''

1620
01:22:40,588 --> 01:22:43,989
WILL YOU WITHDRAW
THE TEACHINGS YOU'VE MADE IN THEM?

1621
01:22:44,259 --> 01:22:46,591
AND HE DIDN'T IMMEDIATELY REPLY.

1622
01:22:46,661 --> 01:22:49,289
HE SAID,
''WELL, YES THEY ARE MY BOOKS

1623
01:22:49,364 --> 01:22:51,525
BUT THERE'S MANY THINGS
WRITTEN THERE

1624
01:22:51,599 --> 01:22:55,330
AND I NEED SOME TIME
TO THINK ABOUT IT.''

1625
01:22:55,403 --> 01:22:58,338
HE ALMOST LOSES HIS NERVE ,
BUT ULTIMATELY HE DOESN'T,

1626
01:22:58,406 --> 01:22:59,964
THE NEXT DAY HE COMES IN

1627
01:23:00,041 --> 01:23:02,942
AND HE STARTS TO PLAY
WITH WORDS AND THEY SAY,

1628
01:23:03,011 --> 01:23:05,479
''ARE ALL THESE YOUR WORKS
AND DO YOU RECANT THEM?''

1629
01:23:05,547 --> 01:23:08,482
HE SAYS, ''DO YOU ASK ME
TO RECANT ALL MY WORKS

1630
01:23:08,550 --> 01:23:09,949
''BECAUSE SOME OF MY WORKS

1631
01:23:10,018 --> 01:23:11,747
''EVERYONE IN THE CHURCH
WOULD AGREE WITH?

1632
01:23:11,820 --> 01:23:13,344
''I'VE WRITTEN AGAINST CERTAIN EVILS

1633
01:23:13,421 --> 01:23:14,979
THAT THE CHURCH
GENERALLY AGREES ARE WRONG.''

1634
01:23:15,056 --> 01:23:16,921
HE'S TRYING
TO GET INTO A DEBATE

1635
01:23:16,992 --> 01:23:18,926
AND THE AUTHORITIES
AREN'T HAVING ANY OF THIS.

1636
01:23:18,994 --> 01:23:20,586
THEY SAY, ''NO, NO, NO.

1637
01:23:20,662 --> 01:23:23,324
YOU JUST HAVE TO SAY-
ARE YOU GOING TO RETRACT THESE?

1638
01:23:23,398 --> 01:23:24,695
ARE YOU GOING TO RECANT?''

1639
01:23:24,766 --> 01:23:26,393
IT'S AN HEROIC MOMENT
ESPECIALLY BECAUSE,

1640
01:23:26,468 --> 01:23:28,026
AS FAR AS LUTHER IS CONCERNED,

1641
01:23:28,303 --> 01:23:30,498
HE BELIEVES
IT'S GOING TO LEAD TO HIS DEATH.

1642
01:23:34,876 --> 01:23:37,709
''UNLESS I AM CONVINCED
BY THE TESTIMONY OF THE SCRIPTURES

1643
01:23:37,779 --> 01:23:39,406
''OR BY CLEAR REASON,

1644
01:23:39,481 --> 01:23:41,676
''FOR I DO NOT TRUST
EITHER IN THE POPE

1645
01:23:41,750 --> 01:23:43,274
''OR IN COUNCILS ALONE,

1646
01:23:43,351 --> 01:23:45,751
''SINCE IT IS WELL KNOWN
THAT THEY HAVE OFTEN ERRED

1647
01:23:45,820 --> 01:23:47,549
''AND CONTRADICTED THEMSELVES,

1648
01:23:47,622 --> 01:23:49,681
''I AM BOUND
BY THE SCRIPTURES I HAVE QUOTED

1649
01:23:49,758 --> 01:23:53,524
''AND MY CONSCIENCE
IS CAPTIVE TO THE WORD OF GOD.

1650
01:23:53,595 --> 01:23:56,860
''I CANNOT AND WILL NOT
RECANT ANYTHING

1651
01:23:56,931 --> 01:24:00,765
''SINCE IT IS NEITHER SAFE NOR RIGHT
TO GO AGAINST CONSCIENCE.

1652
01:24:00,835 --> 01:24:04,327
''HERE I STAND.
I CAN DO NO OTHER.

1653
01:24:04,406 --> 01:24:07,307
MAY GOD HELP ME.
AMEN.''

1654
01:24:07,375 --> 01:24:10,640
THE COUNCIL DID NOT HAVE MUCH
IT COULD SAY IN REPLY.

1655
01:24:10,712 --> 01:24:13,306
LUTHER WAS DECLARED AN OUTLAW.

1656
01:24:13,381 --> 01:24:16,839
HIS LITERATURE WAS BANNED
AND HIS ARREST ORDERED.

1657
01:24:16,918 --> 01:24:20,547
THE DOCUMENT SAID,
''WE WANT HIM TO BE APPREHENDED

1658
01:24:20,622 --> 01:24:23,614
AND TO BE PUNISHED
AS A NOTORIOUS HERETIC.''

1659
01:24:23,691 --> 01:24:25,682
NOW LUTHER
HAD BEEN GIVEN A SAFE CONDUCT

1660
01:24:25,760 --> 01:24:27,694
TO THE DIET OF WORMS,

1661
01:24:27,762 --> 01:24:30,595
JUST AS HUSS HAD BEEN GIVEN
TO THE COUNCIL OF CONSTANCE

1662
01:24:30,665 --> 01:24:32,929
JUST OVER 1 00 YEARS EARLIER.

1663
01:24:33,001 --> 01:24:34,730
AND THERE WERE THOSE AUTHORITIES

1664
01:24:34,803 --> 01:24:36,862
WHO URGED THE HOLY
ROMAN EMPEROR, CHARLES THE V,

1665
01:24:36,938 --> 01:24:38,906
TO IGNORE THE SAFE CONDUCT,

1666
01:24:38,973 --> 01:24:42,966
JUST AS THE EMPEROR SIGISMUND
HAD WITH HUSS' SAFE CONDUCT.

1667
01:24:43,044 --> 01:24:45,706
CHARLES THE V
DIDN'T WANT TO BE KNOWN

1668
01:24:45,780 --> 01:24:47,611
AS THE SECOND EMPEROR
THAT HAD RENEGED

1669
01:24:47,682 --> 01:24:51,914
IN A GOOD-FAITH
CONDUCT PASSAGE AND SO,

1670
01:24:51,986 --> 01:24:53,510
FOR WHATEVER REASON,

1671
01:24:53,588 --> 01:24:54,987
THIS REASON
AND MAYBE SOME OTHERS,

1672
01:24:55,056 --> 01:24:59,891
HE ALLOWED LUTHER
TO LEAVE TOWN AND START HOME.

1673
01:24:59,961 --> 01:25:02,020
THE THOUGHT
WAS HE WOULD PROBABLY BE KILLED

1674
01:25:02,097 --> 01:25:03,621
BY SOMEONE ON THE WAY

1675
01:25:03,698 --> 01:25:05,825
BECAUSE THERE WAS
AN OPEN PRICE ON HIS HEAD.

1676
01:25:05,900 --> 01:25:09,392
INSTEAD, OF COURSE,
LUTHER IS KIDNAPPED

1677
01:25:09,471 --> 01:25:11,564
BY AN ARMED GROUP OF MEN

1678
01:25:11,639 --> 01:25:13,630
WHO WERE ACTUALLY
WORKING FOR FREDERICK THE WISE

1679
01:25:13,708 --> 01:25:15,972
WHO DECIDES HE NEEDS
TO TAKE LUTHER OUT OF CIRCULATION

1680
01:25:16,044 --> 01:25:17,568
FOR A LITTLE WHILE.

1681
01:25:17,645 --> 01:25:18,976
TO WARTBURG CASTLE,

1682
01:25:19,047 --> 01:25:20,605
WHICH THE ELECTOR
FREDERICK KNEW ABOUT

1683
01:25:20,682 --> 01:25:22,616
BUT NOBODY KNEW
WHAT HAD HAPPENED TO LUTHER.

1684
01:25:22,684 --> 01:25:24,515
MANY PEOPLE THOUGHT
THAT HE WAS DEAD.

1685
01:25:24,586 --> 01:25:26,884
FOR THE NEXT YEAR,
FROM THIS LONELY EXILE,

1686
01:25:26,955 --> 01:25:29,719
WHICH LUTHER REFERRED
TO AS 'MY PATMOS',

1687
01:25:29,791 --> 01:25:33,659
THE FORMER PRIEST CONTINUED
HIS WORK OF PROLIFIC WRITING.

1688
01:25:33,728 --> 01:25:36,788
HE EVEN MANAGED
TO TRANSLATE THE NEW TESTAMENT

1689
01:25:36,865 --> 01:25:39,959
FROM GREEK
INTO THE GERMAN LANGUAGE.

1690
01:25:40,034 --> 01:25:41,763
NOW, ABOUT <i>7</i>2 YEARS

1691
01:25:41,836 --> 01:25:45,135
BEFORE LUTHER COMPLETED
